TOPICS COVERED 
Python Basics: Python identifiers, keywords, indentation rules,
Python data types, Variables and dynamic typing, Type conversion
and type checking.
Operators and Input: Operators in Python (Arithmetic, Assignment,
Logical, Relational,), Taking user input from console.
Conditional Statements: if statement, if-else statement, Nested if-
else, elif ladder.

# grading system 
# input --> User name, Marks 
# task --> Assign grades 

name = input("Enter your name: ")
rollNumber = input("Enter your roll Number: ")
mark1 = int(input("Enter your first subject marks: "))
mark2 = int(input("Enter your second subject marks: "))
mark3 = int(input("Enter your third subject marks: "))

total = mark1 + mark2 + mark3
print(total)
percentage = total / 3
print(percentage)

# checking condition 
# if marks of each subject is greater or equal to 40 then print PASS
if mark1 >= 40 and mark2 >= 40 and mark3 >= 40:
    result = 'PASS'
else:
    result = 'FAIL'
    
print(result)    

# Assign grades 
if percentage >= 90:
    grade = 'A+'
elif percentage >= 80:
    grade = 'A'
elif percentage >= 70:
    grade = 'B'
else:
    grade = 'F'
    
print(grade)    
